<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,793,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Head, pronotum, mesoscutum and scutellum creamy yellow with pale brown mottling. Forewings mottled with pale brown between veins, median spot brown without dark brown border. Legs either ochraceous or with dark brown spot at bases of setae.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,793,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[199,371,901,926]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<collectingCountry box="[199,257,901,926]" name="Malta" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Male</collectingCountry>
genitalia.
</emphasis>
Pygofer in lateral view longer than its height, posterior margin conically rounded, macrosetae confined to posterior half. Valve 
<number box="[517,552,937,962]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2.5">2.5</number>
times as wide at base as long. Subgenital plate with terminal fingerlike process 
<number box="[151,200,973,998]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="0.25">0.25</number>
as long as the total length of plate. Style abruptly narrowed in middle, about thrice as long as wide at base, preapical lobe poorly developed; apophysis straight, directed posteriorly. Connective with arms very close to each other and about as long as stem. Aedeagus without basal processes, each shaft bifurcate apically, the longer one (mesal branch) curved anteriorly and the shorter one (lateral branch) directed dorsally, gonopore apical on posterior surface between branches of shaft.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,793,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[199,397,1153,1178]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Female genitalia.</emphasis>
Seventh sternite 
<number box="[589,624,1153,1178]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" value="2.6">2.6</number>
times as broad at base as long medially, posterior margin concave, more strongly so compared to that in 
<taxonomicName box="[505,648,1189,1214]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="distinctus">
<emphasis box="[505,648,1189,1214]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">H. distinctus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and with median notch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,793,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis box="[199,369,1226,1249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Measurements.</emphasis>
