<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1436,793,1718]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1513,1538]" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[321,448,1513,1538]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividens">
<emphasis box="[321,448,1513,1538]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">H. dividens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described from a single male from 
<collectingCountry box="[896,1005,1513,1538]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
(not examined), it is recorded here for the first time from 
<collectingCountry box="[370,431,1549,1574]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">India</collectingCountry>
. This species closely resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Dai, Fletcher and Zhang. These" authorityName="Dai, Fletcher and Zhang. These" box="[800,1295,1549,1574]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[800,926,1549,1574]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">H. pallidus</emphasis>
Dai, Fletcher and Zhang. These
</taxonomicName>
two species can be readily distinguished by the shape of the aedeagal shafts, in 
<taxonomicName box="[907,1034,1585,1610]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dividens">
<emphasis box="[907,1034,1585,1610]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">H. dividens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the shaft is not expanded laterad of gonopores and the lateral fork of aedeagus is more slender where as in 
<taxonomicName box="[969,1095,1621,1646]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Hishimonus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis box="[969,1095,1621,1646]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">H. pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the aedeagal shaft is laterally expanded at level of gonopores in posterior view and the lateral fork of the aedeagal shaft is stouter. This species is associated with 
<taxonomicName authority="Lem." authorityName="Lem." box="[330,622,1693,1718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" genus="Ziziphus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="mauritiana">
<emphasis box="[330,556,1693,1718]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">Ziziphus mauritiana</emphasis>
Lem.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[636,783,1693,1718]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rhamnaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="110" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rhamnaceae</taxonomicName>
) in south 
<collectingCountry box="[893,954,1693,1718]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="110">India</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
